    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.1.3" />
                
                <note type="curatorial">230 Neihardt Collection</note> 
                <fw type="curatorial">3</fw>
                
                
                <opener>
                                                                                            <dateline>New York, Dec. 31, 1900</dateline>
                
                
                    <salute>My dear Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have received your fine letter, and I thank you from my heart for the splendid words of praise which you have given <title>"Pagan Sonnets"</title> and <title>"The Trophies."</title> I was delighted to know that for many years you have liked my work &#8212; it is deeply appreciated, coming from you, one of the greatest poets that America has produced. Every line of yours that I have read has the distinctive seal of genius. Many of your lyrics have never been surpassed. I remember talking about you with George Sterling &#8212; poor George &#8212; many years ago, and how enthusiastic we both were about your poetry. And its<sic>it's</sic> a great regret with me that we should not have known each other before. I should be more than grateful if you could send me your notice of <title>"The Trophies."</title> I have only seen the short excerpt from it in the John Day catalogue, and I feel it will be a real calamity to miss it. I am sending you a copy of the limited edition of <title>"The Trophies"</title> as a small token of my appreciation. With all good wishes, believe me.</p>
                <closer>
                                        <salute>Ever gratefully and sincerely yours,</salute>
                
                                                <signed>John Myers O'Hara.</signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>684 Riverside Drive</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">N. Y.</hi> City</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
